            <Comment>Evidence 1: The variant was identified by target NGS analysis of entire beta globin gene cluster approximately 80.4 kb region on the short arm of chromosome 11, The deletion variant (3'-HBB-HBD-HBG1-HBG2-HBE1-5') was found in a thalassemia patient in compound heterozygous condition with another deletion mutation in (3'-HBB-HBD-5') genomic region . Due to common region of deletion in both alleles there was no sequence reads in HBB-HBD genomic region . Evidence 2: A long stretch of homozygous variant was identified from coordinate ( 5235201 - 5269140) of 33939 bp in variant calling file . Evidence 3: bioinformatic analysis by CNVkit, depthplot and finally IGV analysis shows no read in HBB-HBD region as well as low depth / low read count in the HBB-HBD-HBG1-HBG2-HBE1 genomic region as compare to the neighbouring genomic region. Evidence 4: PCR amplification of HBB gene was failed due to biallelic deletion</Comment>
